## Knowledge Base Tier Structure — DO NOT FLATTEN

The knowledge base at `server/claude/material-takeoff-project/knowledge/` MUST maintain this exact folder structure. **Never move files between tiers. Never inject files alphabetically.**

```
knowledge/
├── tier1-overrides/       ← HIGHEST PRIORITY — Burt Overrides supersede everything
│   └── Burt_Takeoff_Instruction_Updates.pdf
│
├── tier2-process/         ← HOW to do a takeoff (methodology)
│   ├── AI_Bluebeam_Prompt.md
│   ├── Civil_Takeoff_Claude_Prompts.md
│   └── [process PDFs]
│
├── tier3-residential/     ← Residential rules (inject when planType='residential')
│   └── [residential rulebooks, construction manual, etc.]
│
├── tier3-civil/           ← Civil rules (inject when planType='civil')
│   └── [civil drawing guide, utility rulebook, etc.]
│
├── tier3-commercial/      ← Commercial rules (inject when planType='commercial')
│   └── [structural steel, CMU, commercial assemblies]
│
└── shared/                ← Cross-discipline reference files (see injection note below)
    ├── Engineers_Measuring_Tool_Knowledge_Guide.pdf
    ├── Master_Building_Code_Reference_Guide.pdf
    └── 3d-modeling-construction-plans.pdf
```

> **Shared injection note:** Files in `shared/` are NOT automatically injected for every plan type. They are included only when listed in the relevant plan type's doc list in `plan-type-docs.js` (e.g. `DOC_MAP.auto` includes the Engineers guide and 3d-modeling file). To add a shared file to a plan type, add it to the appropriate entry in `plan-type-docs.js` — do not assume it will be picked up automatically.

### Injection Order in System Prompt (MUST be this sequence):
1. `tier1-overrides` — always first, always injected (TIER1_FILES constant)
2. `instructions.txt` — project agent instructions
3. `tier2-process` — always injected (TIER2_CONTEXT constant)
4. `shared` — injected only for plan types that include them in `plan-type-docs.js`
5. `tier3-{planType}` — only the files listed for the matching plan type in `plan-type-docs.js`

---

## Five Architectural Problems & Their Fixes

These were identified defects. Do not revert them.

| # | Problem | Fix |
|---|---------|-----|
| 1 | Files injected alphabetically — Burt Overrides buried | Tier hierarchy in `buildCustomProjectSystemPrompt()` |
| 2 | All docs injected regardless of plan type | `planType` param routes to correct doc list in `plan-type-docs.js` |
| 3 | `plan_processor.py` + `README.md` polluting system prompt | Deleted from knowledge root |
| 4 | 5-page chunking loses civil cross-sheet context | Civil 3-pass flow in `runTakeoffCivil()` |
| 5 | Knowledge re-extracted on every API call | `knowledge-cache.js` warmed at startup in `index.js` |

---

## Plan Type Values

| Value | Knowledge Folder | Takeoff Flow |
|-------|-----------------|-------------|
| `'residential'` | Files listed in `DOC_MAP.residential` in `plan-type-docs.js` | `runTakeoffDefault()` |
| `'civil'` | Files listed in `DOC_MAP.civil` in `plan-type-docs.js` | `runTakeoffCivil()` (3-pass) |
| `'commercial'` | Files listed in `DOC_MAP.commercial` in `plan-type-docs.js` | `runTakeoffDefault()` |
| `'auto'` | Files listed in `DOC_MAP.auto` in `plan-type-docs.js` (NOT full tier3-residential) | `runTakeoffDefault()` |

> **Important:** `auto` does NOT fall back to the full `tier3-residential/` folder. It uses its own curated doc list in `plan-type-docs.js`. When adding a new shared reference for auto mode, add it to `DOC_MAP.auto`, not to `tier3-residential/`.

